Axing a sclass object.

axe-sclass.Rd

sclass objects are byproducts of classbagg objects. Since there are axe functions specific to this class, there is where all documentation related to sclass objects lies.

# S3 method for sclass
axe_call(x, verbose = FALSE, ...)

# S3 method for sclass
axe_env(x, verbose = FALSE, ...)

Arguments

x

sclass object.
verbose

Print information each time an axe method is executed that notes how much memory is released and what functions are disabled. Default is FALSE.
...

Any additional arguments related to axing.

Value

Axed sclass object.

Examples

# Load libraries
suppressWarnings(suppressMessages(library(ipred)))
suppressWarnings(suppressMessages(library(rpart)))
suppressWarnings(suppressMessages(library(MASS)))

# Load data
data("GlaucomaM", package = "TH.data")

classbagg_fit <- bagging(Class ~ ., data = GlaucomaM, coob = TRUE)

butcher(classbagg_fit$mtrees[[1]])
